article.headline: Dartmouth beats Cornell 42-7
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Dalyn Williams threw for three touchdowns and ran for another, Kyle Bramble had a 39-yard scoring run Saturday, and Dartmouth beat winless Cornell 42-7. Williams was 23 of 33 for 321 yards, with scoring passes of 24 yards to Bramble, 32 yards to Victor Williams and 30 yards to Ryan McManus. Williams, who last season ran for more yards than any Dartmouth quarterback ever (563), scored on a 9-yard run in the second quarter and gained 62 yards on six carries. Bramble gained 89 yards on eight carries for the Big Green (6-2, 4-1 Ivy League), and had four catches for 68 yards. Victor Williams caught seven passes for 101 yards Cornell (0-8, 0-5) capped its opening drive with a 48-yard TD run by Luke Hagy, but it was all Dartmouth after that. The Big Green outgained the Big Red to 583-308 and finished with a goal-line stand.
